    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi Artur, the new API has been implemented in the dev version by PR https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/17481, and will be available in next release. There is a related issue https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/16366 requesting the rich status error details. Examples and documentation will be added soon.\r\n\r\nHere is a short snippet demonstrate the usage of the new rich status API `abort_with_status`:\r\n```Python\r\n# Server side\r\nfrom grpc_status import rpc_status\r\nfrom google.protobuf import any_pb2\r\n\r\ndef ...Servicer(...):\r\n    def ARPCCall(request, context):\r\n        ...\r\n        detail = any_pb2.Any()\r\n        detail.Pack(\r\n            rpc_status.error_details_pb2.DebugInfo(\r\n                stack_entries=traceback.format_stack(),\r\n                detail=\"Can't recognize this argument\",\r\n            )\r\n        )\r\n        rich_status = grpc_status.status_pb2.Status(\r\n            code=grpc_status.code_pb2.INVALID_ARGUMENT,\r\n            message='API call quota depleted',\r\n            details=[detail]\r\n        )\r\n        context.abort_with_status(rpc_status.to_status(rich_status))\r\n        # The method handler will abort\r\n```\r\nTo learn more about the design, here is the [gRFC](https://github.com/grpc/proposal/pull/118), comments are welcomed."
